  <h3>Key Terminology</h3>

  <p>Spanish rice cuisine comes with its own vocabulary, essential for understanding recipes and techniques:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sofrito</strong> - The aromatic base of tomatoes, garlic, and sometimes peppers, slowly cooked to concentrate flavor</li>
    <li><strong>Fumet</strong> - Fish or seafood stock used as the cooking liquid</li>
    <li><strong>Caldo</strong> - Meat or vegetable broth</li>
    <li><strong>Señoret</strong> - Seafood that has been cleaned and prepared for direct incorporation into rice</li>
    <li><strong>Garrofón</strong> - Large white bean traditional in paella Valenciana</li>
    <li><strong>Ferraura</strong> - Flat green bean, another traditional paella ingredient</li>
  </ul>

